WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.401 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.401 --> 00:00:07.335 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.335 --> 00:00:19.080 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.080 --> 00:00:21.660 align:middle line:84%
>> At the beginning
of the 1900s,

00:00:21.660 --> 00:00:26.760 align:middle line:84%
humanity was being influenced
by photographs, newspapers,

00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:31.680 align:middle line:90%
stage plays, and silent films.

00:00:31.680 --> 00:00:34.770 align:middle line:10%
During the 1930s,
the major studios

00:00:34.770 --> 00:00:37.980 align:middle line:10%
began creating motion
pictures with sound,

00:00:37.980 --> 00:00:42.030 align:middle line:10%
bringing these stories
closer to real life.

00:00:42.030 --> 00:00:46.080 align:middle line:10%
By the 1960s, color television
became a novelty item

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:48.570 align:middle line:10%
for several families.

00:00:48.570 --> 00:00:52.980 align:middle line:84%
Thousands of people could
be influenced simultaneously

00:00:52.980 --> 00:00:55.650 align:middle line:84%
by highly edited
stories, giving them

00:00:55.650 --> 00:00:58.290 align:middle line:84%
a longer glimpse into
alternate realities

00:00:58.290 --> 00:01:02.880 align:middle line:84%
that stage plays and
artwork couldn't do.

00:01:02.880 --> 00:01:05.550 align:middle line:90%
The race for space was underway.

00:01:05.550 --> 00:01:08.700 align:middle line:10%
And humans began wondering
if contact with other worlds

00:01:08.700 --> 00:01:12.300 align:middle line:10%
could actually be possible.

00:01:12.300 --> 00:01:15.450 align:middle line:84%
As the late 1960s
swept the planet,

00:01:15.450 --> 00:01:19.710 align:middle line:84%
more and more humans began
to awaken to the possibility

00:01:19.710 --> 00:01:21.630 align:middle line:90%
of a greater reality.

00:01:21.630 --> 00:01:24.540 align:middle line:84%
And the shades were opened
on the occult secrets

00:01:24.540 --> 00:01:26.130 align:middle line:90%
held in the libraries.

00:01:26.130 --> 00:01:30.801 align:middle line:84%
And new messages began
filling the shelves.

00:01:30.801 --> 00:01:34.020 align:middle line:84%
Channel texts became
more and more available.

00:01:34.020 --> 00:01:36.690 align:middle line:10%
And the occult labels
and misconceptions

00:01:36.690 --> 00:01:40.260 align:middle line:10%
about this mysterious form
of spiritual communication

00:01:40.260 --> 00:01:42.910 align:middle line:10%
began piling up.

00:01:42.910 --> 00:01:45.080 align:middle line:10%
It was becoming a phenomenon.

00:01:45.080 --> 00:01:48.750 align:middle line:90%


00:01:48.750 --> 00:01:51.960 align:middle line:84%
>> My interest in the occult
began when I was growing up

00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:55.650 align:middle line:84%
in the 1970s in the borough
of Queens in New York City.

00:01:55.650 --> 00:01:59.280 align:middle line:10%
I was fascinated with mythology
and folklore, the paranormal,

00:01:59.280 --> 00:02:00.630 align:middle line:10%
the supernatural.

00:02:00.630 --> 00:02:03.030 align:middle line:84%
I vividly remember
my sister coming home

00:02:03.030 --> 00:02:06.420 align:middle line:84%
with books about Bigfoot
and flying saucers

00:02:06.420 --> 00:02:09.570 align:middle line:84%
and the works of
Carlos Castaneda.

00:02:09.570 --> 00:02:12.120 align:middle line:84%
I was very interested
in astrology.

00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:16.370 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to know where
all this came from.

00:02:16.370 --> 00:02:18.860 align:middle line:10%
>> I grew up in a house
that was so haunted,

00:02:18.860 --> 00:02:20.900 align:middle line:10%
you would set something
down, turn around,

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:21.950 align:middle line:10%
it would disappear.

00:02:21.950 --> 00:02:23.793 align:middle line:84%
We'd be watching TV,
back in the old days,

00:02:23.793 --> 00:02:25.460 align:middle line:84%
where there was a
physical dial that you

00:02:25.460 --> 00:02:28.880 align:middle line:84%
had to stand up, walk across
the room, and turn the knob.

00:02:28.880 --> 00:02:31.910 align:middle line:84%
Well, while we're sitting
down on the couch watching TV,

00:02:31.910 --> 00:02:34.500 align:middle line:90%
the knob would turn.

00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:36.440 align:middle line:84%
We would hear footsteps
going up and down

00:02:36.440 --> 00:02:39.080 align:middle line:84%
the hallway, toilets
flushing downstairs when

00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:39.980 align:middle line:90%
we were upstairs.

00:02:39.980 --> 00:02:44.840 align:middle line:84%
It was just so overwhelmingly
paranormal, it was crazy.

00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:46.400 align:middle line:84%
When I started
telling my parents,

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:48.290 align:middle line:84%
I'm seeing these things,
I'm communicating

00:02:48.290 --> 00:02:50.360 align:middle line:84%
with these things, my
parents were like, OK.

00:02:50.360 --> 00:02:53.180 align:middle line:84%
We need to go back to our
old church, which turned out

00:02:53.180 --> 00:02:56.690 align:middle line:84%
to be a spiritualist church,
which is your typical stand up,

00:02:56.690 --> 00:02:59.120 align:middle line:84%
sit down, stand up, sit
down, stand up, sing.

00:02:59.120 --> 00:03:03.620 align:middle line:84%
But services ended when one
to three mediums would go up

00:03:03.620 --> 00:03:06.620 align:middle line:84%
on stage, go into a
deep trance, and spirits

00:03:06.620 --> 00:03:08.330 align:middle line:90%
would channel through them.

00:03:08.330 --> 00:03:11.040 align:middle line:84%
Every Saturday night
in the church basement,

00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:13.100 align:middle line:90%
we were doing seances.

00:03:13.100 --> 00:03:15.320 align:middle line:90%
I grew up with this everywhere.

00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:19.010 align:middle line:84%
Now, mind you, also, my parents'
basement was full of books.

00:03:19.010 --> 00:03:21.770 align:middle line:84%
I could read about
anything that I wanted to.

00:03:21.770 --> 00:03:24.470 align:middle line:84%
And one of the books that
stuck out the most to me

00:03:24.470 --> 00:03:27.650 align:middle line:84%
was Manly P. Hall's "Secret
Teaching of all Ages."

00:03:27.650 --> 00:03:30.140 align:middle line:84%
And as a young teenager,
I'm devouring this book,

00:03:30.140 --> 00:03:31.010 align:middle line:90%
going, wow.

00:03:31.010 --> 00:03:32.450 align:middle line:84%
These are the secrets
that I've been after.

00:03:32.450 --> 00:03:34.867 align:middle line:84%
This is what the Whisperers
have been talking to me about.

00:03:34.867 --> 00:03:35.910 align:middle line:90%
Whisperers were my guide.

00:03:35.910 --> 00:03:36.710 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, I get it.

00:03:36.710 --> 00:03:39.467 align:middle line:84%
Somebody's writing
about this stuff.

00:03:39.467 --> 00:03:41.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, growing up Christian,
we believed the Bible was

00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:43.540 align:middle line:90%
channeled by the Holy Spirit.

00:03:43.540 --> 00:03:45.460 align:middle line:90%
We just didn't use that word.

00:03:45.460 --> 00:03:48.820 align:middle line:10%
The word "channeling" is usually
associated with the occult

00:03:48.820 --> 00:03:51.400 align:middle line:10%
and mysticism and
things that religion

00:03:51.400 --> 00:03:53.710 align:middle line:10%
tends to shy away from.

00:03:53.710 --> 00:03:56.415 align:middle line:84%
But if you ask any good
Christian to explain

00:03:56.415 --> 00:03:57.790 align:middle line:84%
how the Bible is
written, they'll

00:03:57.790 --> 00:04:00.280 align:middle line:84%
say, oh, the Holy Spirit
possessed one's mind

00:04:00.280 --> 00:04:03.640 align:middle line:84%
without them knowing it
and wrote through them

00:04:03.640 --> 00:04:05.963 align:middle line:84%
the words that it
wanted to write.

00:04:05.963 --> 00:04:08.380 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, that sounds
a whole lot like channeling.

00:04:08.380 --> 00:04:10.720 align:middle line:84%
So it's really just different
words for the same thing.

00:04:10.720 --> 00:04:13.570 align:middle line:84%
If you want to call
it "inspiration,"

00:04:13.570 --> 00:04:15.170 align:middle line:90%
that word can be used as well.

00:04:15.170 --> 00:04:18.370 align:middle line:84%
But I think, especially
in religious circles,

00:04:18.370 --> 00:04:21.709 align:middle line:84%
the word "channeling" inspires
occultism and things like that.

00:04:21.709 --> 00:04:24.850 align:middle line:84%
So they think it's a
word that's off-limits.

00:04:24.850 --> 00:04:27.700 align:middle line:84%
But it's actually, in my
estimation, exactly what

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:30.490 align:middle line:90%
they believe of the Bible.

00:04:30.490 --> 00:04:34.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Several legendary stories
throughout religion have been

00:04:34.540 --> 00:04:38.920 align:middle line:84%
delivered through humans hearing
voices and carving or writing

00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:41.010 align:middle line:90%
down the messages.

00:04:41.010 --> 00:04:44.790 align:middle line:10%
This practice continued,
as oracles, prophets,

00:04:44.790 --> 00:04:48.780 align:middle line:10%
and poets shared their
messages through pen and paper

00:04:48.780 --> 00:04:51.900 align:middle line:10%
and eventually the typewriter.

00:04:51.900 --> 00:04:54.450 align:middle line:84%
The practice of
automatic writing

00:04:54.450 --> 00:04:58.630 align:middle line:84%
is another highly debated
form of channeling that has

00:04:58.630 --> 00:05:00.830 align:middle line:90%
several different meanings.

00:05:00.830 --> 00:05:03.170 align:middle line:90%
But the question remains.

00:05:03.170 --> 00:05:08.290 align:middle line:84%
Who is moving the hands
and writing the message?

00:05:08.290 --> 00:05:11.110 align:middle line:84%
>> In terms of the modern
age, automatic writing is one

00:05:11.110 --> 00:05:13.600 align:middle line:84%
of the most popular
forms of mediumship.

00:05:13.600 --> 00:05:16.780 align:middle line:84%
And it was very popular
in the United States

00:05:16.780 --> 00:05:20.050 align:middle line:84%
and Europe, going back
to the mid-19th century,

00:05:20.050 --> 00:05:24.040 align:middle line:84%
where an individual seated with
a piece of paper and a writing

00:05:24.040 --> 00:05:27.280 align:middle line:84%
implement, would feel that he
or she was receiving some kind

00:05:27.280 --> 00:05:28.990 align:middle line:90%
of extra physical information.

00:05:28.990 --> 00:05:32.560 align:middle line:84%
And probably the most popular
channel text in modern history,

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:35.410 align:middle line:84%
"A Course in Miracles," can
be considered the result

00:05:35.410 --> 00:05:37.330 align:middle line:90%
of automatic writing.

00:05:37.330 --> 00:05:40.330 align:middle line:10%
A research psychologist
named Helen Schucman

00:05:40.330 --> 00:05:42.910 align:middle line:10%
at Columbia University
in the 1960s

00:05:42.910 --> 00:05:45.520 align:middle line:10%
began to hear
clairaudient voices.

00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:50.710 align:middle line:84%
And she composed an
extraordinary comprehensive

00:05:50.710 --> 00:05:54.190 align:middle line:84%
complex spiritual
psychology that

00:05:54.190 --> 00:05:56.860 align:middle line:84%
later came to be called
"A Course in Miracles."

00:05:56.860 --> 00:06:00.310 align:middle line:84%
And it's probably the
most popular channel text

00:06:00.310 --> 00:06:03.350 align:middle line:90%
in modern history.

00:06:03.350 --> 00:06:06.980 align:middle line:10%
>> There's nothing that I would
call ordinary audition about

00:06:06.980 --> 00:06:08.385 align:middle line:10%
this at all.

00:06:08.385 --> 00:06:09.260 align:middle line:10%
It's a curious thing.

00:06:09.260 --> 00:06:10.970 align:middle line:10%
And it will be very
difficult to explain.

00:06:10.970 --> 00:06:14.760 align:middle line:10%
Somebody asked me, was it as
though your hand was moving?

00:06:14.760 --> 00:06:15.560 align:middle line:10%
No.

00:06:15.560 --> 00:06:20.180 align:middle line:10%
I wrote perfectly
voluntarily, in response to--

00:06:20.180 --> 00:06:23.450 align:middle line:10%
I call it a voice, but
a voice has sounds--

00:06:23.450 --> 00:06:26.660 align:middle line:10%
or sounds as though it has
something to do with hearing.

00:06:26.660 --> 00:06:28.400 align:middle line:10%
I didn't hear anything.

00:06:28.400 --> 00:06:32.990 align:middle line:10%
I think it's the sort of hearing
that you can't really describe.

00:06:32.990 --> 00:06:36.050 align:middle line:10%
It doesn't have anything
to do with ears or waves

00:06:36.050 --> 00:06:38.870 align:middle line:10%
hitting a drum or
anything on that order.

00:06:38.870 --> 00:06:39.780 align:middle line:90%
I don't really know.

00:06:39.780 --> 00:06:43.280 align:middle line:84%
I think maybe I'm using the
wrong word when I say "hear."

00:06:43.280 --> 00:06:47.690 align:middle line:84%
I think "knew" may be a
better word than "heard."

00:06:47.690 --> 00:06:50.120 align:middle line:90%
I sort of recognized it.

00:06:50.120 --> 00:06:54.380 align:middle line:84%
It came very easily, very
rapidly, very smoothly.

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:57.200 align:middle line:10%
If I didn't catch a phrase, I
could sort of say "would you

00:06:57.200 --> 00:07:00.860 align:middle line:10%
mind doing that again?"

00:07:00.860 --> 00:07:02.420 align:middle line:10%
>> The story is
truly remarkable,

00:07:02.420 --> 00:07:05.600 align:middle line:10%
in that Helen Schucman,
in the early 1960s,

00:07:05.600 --> 00:07:07.880 align:middle line:10%
she was working with
a colleague, Dr.

00:07:07.880 --> 00:07:09.050 align:middle line:10%
William Thetford.

00:07:09.050 --> 00:07:11.300 align:middle line:10%
And they had worked together
for many, many years

00:07:11.300 --> 00:07:13.220 align:middle line:10%
in this field of psychology.

00:07:13.220 --> 00:07:16.850 align:middle line:84%
Helen Schucman began having
psychic dreams, very, very

00:07:16.850 --> 00:07:20.180 align:middle line:84%
vivid dreams that she said it
"felt like some kind of entity

00:07:20.180 --> 00:07:21.622 align:middle line:90%
was contacting me."

00:07:21.622 --> 00:07:23.330 align:middle line:84%
And for her, being an
atheist, of course,

00:07:23.330 --> 00:07:25.010 align:middle line:84%
this felt very
bizarre and she almost

00:07:25.010 --> 00:07:26.930 align:middle line:84%
didn't wanna tell
anybody about it.

00:07:26.930 --> 00:07:29.880 align:middle line:84%
But she confided in
her colleague and said,

00:07:29.880 --> 00:07:32.390 align:middle line:84%
I'm having these dreams
of an entity coming

00:07:32.390 --> 00:07:35.180 align:middle line:84%
to me that wants to
bring a message through

00:07:35.180 --> 00:07:38.490 align:middle line:84%
and it feels like it
has a lot of authority.

00:07:38.490 --> 00:07:40.550 align:middle line:84%
And I want to obey it,
but I don't know how

00:07:40.550 --> 00:07:42.780 align:middle line:90%
to bring this message through.

00:07:42.780 --> 00:07:45.800 align:middle line:84%
And so William said, well,
next time you get this message,

00:07:45.800 --> 00:07:48.500 align:middle line:84%
just say yes to it
and start writing.

00:07:48.500 --> 00:07:50.610 align:middle line:90%
And we'll read it together.

00:07:50.610 --> 00:07:52.760 align:middle line:84%
And if it sounds crazy,
we'll throw it in the fire

00:07:52.760 --> 00:07:54.560 align:middle line:90%
and never talk about it.

00:07:54.560 --> 00:07:56.780 align:middle line:90%
So that's what Helen did.

00:07:56.780 --> 00:07:58.730 align:middle line:84%
The first message of
"A Course in Miracles"

00:07:58.730 --> 00:08:01.220 align:middle line:84%
came through, which
Helen describes

00:08:01.220 --> 00:08:03.770 align:middle line:84%
as "an inner voice"
that spoke to her

00:08:03.770 --> 00:08:06.050 align:middle line:84%
and said, "This is a
course in miracles.

00:08:06.050 --> 00:08:08.670 align:middle line:90%
Please take notes."

00:08:08.670 --> 00:08:10.790 align:middle line:10%
>> This is strictly mental.

00:08:10.790 --> 00:08:13.490 align:middle line:10%
Otherwise, I would consider
it hallucinatory activity.

00:08:13.490 --> 00:08:15.740 align:middle line:10%
I don't feel it was that.

00:08:15.740 --> 00:08:17.250 align:middle line:10%
It wasn't my voice.

00:08:17.250 --> 00:08:19.130 align:middle line:10%
It couldn't have
been, because it

00:08:19.130 --> 00:08:24.920 align:middle line:10%
talked about a whole area with
which I am entirely unfamiliar.

00:08:24.920 --> 00:08:26.660 align:middle line:10%
For some reason
or other, it never

00:08:26.660 --> 00:08:29.360 align:middle line:10%
occurred to me not to do this.

00:08:29.360 --> 00:08:30.980 align:middle line:10%
I thought that this
should be done.

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:34.309 align:middle line:10%
I made every effort
to keep it without me.

00:08:34.309 --> 00:08:36.110 align:middle line:10%
I did not want to intrude on it.

00:08:36.110 --> 00:08:41.659 align:middle line:10%
And I felt that it was a matter
of personal integrity not to.

00:08:41.659 --> 00:08:45.520 align:middle line:10%
I really did not
interfere with it.

00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:49.590 align:middle line:10%
>> And so she wrote for seven
years, almost every day,

00:08:49.590 --> 00:08:52.920 align:middle line:10%
chapter upon chapter of
a book that's, to many

00:08:52.920 --> 00:08:56.970 align:middle line:10%
people's opinion, probably the
most profound channeled work

00:08:56.970 --> 00:09:00.960 align:middle line:10%
ever came through her,
which was a sort of form

00:09:00.960 --> 00:09:06.510 align:middle line:10%
of psychotherapy, using the
biblical gospel language that

00:09:06.510 --> 00:09:09.300 align:middle line:10%
lays down this philosophy
of how to be in the world,

00:09:09.300 --> 00:09:12.810 align:middle line:10%
how to see one another
as one, not separate,

00:09:12.810 --> 00:09:15.757 align:middle line:10%
and how forgiveness actually
is the path to heaven,

00:09:15.757 --> 00:09:18.090 align:middle line:10%
that the only way to get to
heaven is through the person

00:09:18.090 --> 00:09:19.290 align:middle line:10%
right in front of me.

00:09:19.290 --> 00:09:21.810 align:middle line:84%
Because heaven is
entered two by two.

00:09:21.810 --> 00:09:23.790 align:middle line:84%
And Helen herself
said she wasn't

00:09:23.790 --> 00:09:25.620 align:middle line:90%
the best student of the course.

00:09:25.620 --> 00:09:28.050 align:middle line:84%
She wasn't very good at
living this philosophy, which,

00:09:28.050 --> 00:09:31.560 align:middle line:84%
to me, just speaks even
more about the validity

00:09:31.560 --> 00:09:33.900 align:middle line:84%
of the channeling itself,
that this wasn't something

00:09:33.900 --> 00:09:36.310 align:middle line:90%
she could've made up herself.

00:09:36.310 --> 00:09:38.850 align:middle line:84%
>> I think the thing that I
found upsetting about it was it

00:09:38.850 --> 00:09:40.720 align:middle line:84%
went against
everything I believe,

00:09:40.720 --> 00:09:42.900 align:middle line:90%
which is very hard to do.

00:09:42.900 --> 00:09:46.470 align:middle line:84%
But I felt it was
much more important--

00:09:46.470 --> 00:09:47.770 align:middle line:90%
I know what I believe.

00:09:47.770 --> 00:09:51.180 align:middle line:10%
But I didn't know what
this was going to do next.

00:09:51.180 --> 00:09:54.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Schucman identified
herself as the scribe,

00:09:54.330 --> 00:09:56.040 align:middle line:90%
but not as the author.

00:09:56.040 --> 00:10:00.070 align:middle line:84%
And she made this work
freely available to people.

00:10:00.070 --> 00:10:03.480 align:middle line:84%
And it first began circulating
through small study groups

00:10:03.480 --> 00:10:06.630 align:middle line:84%
and then, later, was
published in the early 1970s

00:10:06.630 --> 00:10:10.450 align:middle line:84%
and went on to become
a worldwide phenomenon.

00:10:10.450 --> 00:10:14.130 align:middle line:84%
>> There are a number of reasons
that "A Course in Miracles"

00:10:14.130 --> 00:10:16.950 align:middle line:84%
displays so much spiritual
genius in the way that

00:10:16.950 --> 00:10:18.030 align:middle line:90%
it's written.

00:10:18.030 --> 00:10:20.070 align:middle line:84%
One can read this
text and, even if you

00:10:20.070 --> 00:10:22.020 align:middle line:84%
don't know the
language yet, you can

00:10:22.020 --> 00:10:23.340 align:middle line:90%
read it and go, my goodness.

00:10:23.340 --> 00:10:24.390 align:middle line:90%
This is profound.

00:10:24.390 --> 00:10:26.610 align:middle line:84%
There's something
alive in this text

00:10:26.610 --> 00:10:28.380 align:middle line:90%
and it starts to pull on you.

00:10:28.380 --> 00:10:31.450 align:middle line:84%
And you want to learn
the language system.

00:10:31.450 --> 00:10:34.380 align:middle line:84%
And so the "Course" is
a truly channel text

00:10:34.380 --> 00:10:37.980 align:middle line:84%
in that, just like all
true channel texts,

00:10:37.980 --> 00:10:40.650 align:middle line:84%
it will meet you where you're
at, spiritually speaking.

00:10:40.650 --> 00:10:43.740 align:middle line:84%
And you'll understand what
you're ready to understand.

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:45.870 align:middle line:84%
But the deeper you go
in your development,

00:10:45.870 --> 00:10:47.550 align:middle line:90%
the deeper the book goes.

00:10:47.550 --> 00:10:49.950 align:middle line:84%
And so that's why
channeled text, especially

00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:52.770 align:middle line:84%
like "A Course in
Miracles," are texts

00:10:52.770 --> 00:10:55.980 align:middle line:84%
that people return to
again and again for decades

00:10:55.980 --> 00:10:57.460 align:middle line:90%
and decades of their life.

00:10:57.460 --> 00:10:59.940 align:middle line:84%
And every time you read it,
it feels like you've never

00:10:59.940 --> 00:11:02.970 align:middle line:90%
read it before.

00:11:02.970 --> 00:11:05.130 align:middle line:84%
>> But I hadn't
caught up with it yet.

00:11:05.130 --> 00:11:06.900 align:middle line:10%
And I don't understand it.

00:11:06.900 --> 00:11:10.260 align:middle line:10%
And I still feel
very baffled by it.

00:11:10.260 --> 00:11:13.350 align:middle line:10%
I do think, and under
certain circumstances,

00:11:13.350 --> 00:11:15.450 align:middle line:10%
I think there are
questions I could probably

00:11:15.450 --> 00:11:17.610 align:middle line:10%
write an answer to.

00:11:17.610 --> 00:11:20.820 align:middle line:10%
According to the
"Course," we should

00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:25.950 align:middle line:10%
and everyone could ask about
anything and get an answer.

00:11:25.950 --> 00:11:29.060 align:middle line:90%


00:11:29.060 --> 00:11:33.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, even if one takes a hard
core materialist view of life

00:11:33.680 --> 00:11:37.190 align:middle line:84%
and says, look, there's no
such thing as extra physical

00:11:37.190 --> 00:11:38.270 align:middle line:90%
cognition.

00:11:38.270 --> 00:11:39.890 align:middle line:90%
That's all delusion.

00:11:39.890 --> 00:11:42.680 align:middle line:84%
She was writing this
down from her own psyche,

00:11:42.680 --> 00:11:46.710 align:middle line:84%
from her own subconscious,
let's go with that for a moment.

00:11:46.710 --> 00:11:49.340 align:middle line:84%
Let's go with the
materialist point of view.

00:11:49.340 --> 00:11:54.290 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't reduce, by one
iota, the extraordinary nature

00:11:54.290 --> 00:11:56.540 align:middle line:90%
of Schucman's accomplishment.

00:11:56.540 --> 00:12:02.930 align:middle line:84%
If a work as complex, as
moving, as rich, as insightful

00:12:02.930 --> 00:12:07.550 align:middle line:84%
as "A Course in Miracles"
came from the subconscious

00:12:07.550 --> 00:12:12.110 align:middle line:84%
of a research psychologist,
a self-professed atheist, who

00:12:12.110 --> 00:12:16.220 align:middle line:84%
just sat down and
took notes, what

00:12:16.220 --> 00:12:19.940 align:middle line:84%
does that tell us
about the unknown folds

00:12:19.940 --> 00:12:21.530 align:middle line:90%
of our own psyches?

00:12:21.530 --> 00:12:25.220 align:middle line:84%
At a certain point, the
materialist or immaterialist

00:12:25.220 --> 00:12:28.820 align:middle line:84%
argument almost
becomes irrelevant.

00:12:28.820 --> 00:12:36.170 align:middle line:84%
Does it really matter whether a
skeptic or I agree or disagree

00:12:36.170 --> 00:12:37.550 align:middle line:90%
about the nature of the source?

00:12:37.550 --> 00:12:40.220 align:middle line:90%
Look at the result.

00:12:40.220 --> 00:12:43.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Another influential woman
who was raised near the famous

00:12:43.910 --> 00:12:49.490 align:middle line:84%
Burned Over District in upstate
New York was Jane Roberts.

00:12:49.490 --> 00:12:53.960 align:middle line:84%
In the early 1960s, she and
her partner, Robert Butts,

00:12:53.960 --> 00:12:58.362 align:middle line:84%
began experimenting
with a Ouija board.

00:12:58.362 --> 00:12:59.570 align:middle line:10%
>> We borrowed a Ouija board.

00:12:59.570 --> 00:13:02.030 align:middle line:10%
We didn't even buy one.

00:13:02.030 --> 00:13:06.140 align:middle line:10%
And after, I forget, once
or twice or something,

00:13:06.140 --> 00:13:08.600 align:middle line:10%
we started to get
stuck on the board.

00:13:08.600 --> 00:13:11.940 align:middle line:10%
The pointer would go over the
alphabet and spell messages.

00:13:11.940 --> 00:13:12.740 align:middle line:10%
>> OK.

00:13:12.740 --> 00:13:16.700 align:middle line:10%
>> And after a while, the
messages said they came from

00:13:16.700 --> 00:13:19.730 align:middle line:10%
a personality called "Seth."

00:13:19.730 --> 00:13:21.710 align:middle line:10%
The first thing I
thought of was, well,

00:13:21.710 --> 00:13:23.720 align:middle line:10%
it's the subconscious.

00:13:23.720 --> 00:13:25.590 align:middle line:10%
Robert's pushing it
or Robert's saying--

00:13:25.590 --> 00:13:25.880 align:middle line:10%
>> Yeah.

00:13:25.880 --> 00:13:26.700 align:middle line:10%
>> --I was pushing it.

00:13:26.700 --> 00:13:28.040 align:middle line:10%
So we went through that long--

00:13:28.040 --> 00:13:28.840 align:middle line:10%
>> Yes.

00:13:28.840 --> 00:13:29.790 align:middle line:10%
>> --kind of thing.

00:13:29.790 --> 00:13:35.930 align:middle line:10%
And after only maybe five or
six, seven sessions with it,

00:13:35.930 --> 00:13:37.940 align:middle line:10%
Seth came through vocally.

00:13:37.940 --> 00:13:40.520 align:middle line:10%
I would start to know
what was going to be said.

00:13:40.520 --> 00:13:43.190 align:middle line:10%
And then, I would
start to want to speak.

00:13:43.190 --> 00:13:46.730 align:middle line:10%
I just began speaking
the words automatically,

00:13:46.730 --> 00:13:51.260 align:middle line:10%
for Seth, without
knowing what I was saying

00:13:51.260 --> 00:13:53.600 align:middle line:10%
until I came out of trance.

00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:57.470 align:middle line:10%
There was no training per se
for this, no self-hypnosis,

00:13:57.470 --> 00:13:58.270 align:middle line:10%
nothing.

00:13:58.270 --> 00:13:59.370 align:middle line:90%
It just came.

00:13:59.370 --> 00:14:01.280 align:middle line:90%
Although, I did give consent.

00:14:01.280 --> 00:14:05.420 align:middle line:10%
That is-- had I not wanted to do
it, it wouldn't have happened.

00:14:05.420 --> 00:14:06.890 align:middle line:10%
But I was so curious.

00:14:06.890 --> 00:14:10.580 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to know
what was happening.

00:14:10.580 --> 00:14:13.700 align:middle line:84%
>> The revolutionary
book "Seth Speaks"

00:14:13.700 --> 00:14:17.870 align:middle line:84%
was published in the early
1970s and went on to become part

00:14:17.870 --> 00:14:23.120 align:middle line:84%
