00:18:29.690 --> 00:18:31.760 align:middle line:84%
And they're clamping
down on what

00:18:31.760 --> 00:18:33.470 align:middle line:90%
spiritual practice has to be.

00:18:33.470 --> 00:18:35.660 align:middle line:84%
So people were now
open and trying

00:18:35.660 --> 00:18:37.670 align:middle line:84%
to explore some of
this extra material.

00:18:37.670 --> 00:18:41.360 align:middle line:84%
They wanted to know what
the nature of spirituality

00:18:41.360 --> 00:18:43.100 align:middle line:90%
versus religion was.

00:18:43.100 --> 00:18:45.650 align:middle line:84%
So "The Seth Material"
came in at the right time

00:18:45.650 --> 00:18:48.020 align:middle line:84%
to actually spawn
that New Age movement

00:18:48.020 --> 00:18:51.470 align:middle line:84%
that the spiritual world
can be peace, love,

00:18:51.470 --> 00:18:54.590 align:middle line:84%
and light and happiness, that
you can achieve these higher

00:18:54.590 --> 00:18:57.980 align:middle line:84%
states of being without
the rigorous orthodoxy,

00:18:57.980 --> 00:19:01.190 align:middle line:84%
that you can be that
conduit of spiritual growth,

00:19:01.190 --> 00:19:05.040 align:middle line:84%
rather than some church telling
that you have to do it our way

00:19:05.040 --> 00:19:06.200 align:middle line:90%
and that's the only way.

00:19:06.200 --> 00:19:08.420 align:middle line:84%
So the timing of
"Seth's Material"

00:19:08.420 --> 00:19:11.540 align:middle line:84%
was perfect to spawn this
whole New Age movement,

00:19:11.540 --> 00:19:13.430 align:middle line:84%
so that we could actually
tune in and become

00:19:13.430 --> 00:19:16.210 align:middle line:90%
our own spiritual teachers.

00:19:16.210 --> 00:19:18.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, I don't call
